* text=auto

*.py text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.jsonl text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf

*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.zip binary

# Shipped proof bundles are byte-exact: their manifest.sha256, viewer.html, and
# audit chain are hashed at seal time, so ANY line-ending conversion on checkout
# breaks offline verification (viewer.html byte/SHA mismatch, manifest.sha256 no
# longer equals "<sha>  manifest.json\n"). Disable all EOL/text munging for the
# example bundles so a fresh clone on any OS verifies VALID.
examples/public-run-complete/** -text
examples/public-run-partial/** -text
